Vintage style: A dramatic birds-eye view of an old wooden filing cabinet drawer pulled open, revealing hundreds of paper document fragments scattered chaotically across a worn oak desk surface. Some fragments are connected by thin red threads like a detective's evidence board. The papers show aged, yellowed edges with coffee stains. A magnifying glass rests among the scattered pieces. Warm sepia lighting casts long shadows across the scene, with dust particles visible in the afternoon sunlight streaming through a venetian blind. The composition emphasizes the overwhelming disorder and the detective-like investigation needed to piece everything together.
